First, can you give me more information about this symptom?
> 'Flutter SDK PATH' cannot be identified.

I'm not sure what that means. Another screen shot would probably help.

Second, since MacOS treats ~/Library specially, could you try installing the Flutter SDK in a different place, just to see if Flutter is getting tripped up by the special directory?

@guominfang Thanks for the info. I'm not sure this is actually a problem. Those errors have been there since the plugin was created. There is an experimental option that causes them to go away, but the recommended way to edit Android code is to open the Android module as a project in its own window.

Does your Flutter app run? If it runs then this is working as expected (not as wanted, but it's a compromise).

@stevemessick Not to highjack the discussion, but since I get same errors, I'd like to add that my Flutter app runs indeed, but ONLY if I remove
```
<meta-data
            android:name="flutterEmbedding"
            android:value="2" />
```
in manifest. Otherwise I can't use any of the Java code that I need for my app (which is in Flutter), with those lines present I can't use MethodChannel, nothing is recognized and it's a cascade of errors. Comment those two lines out - everything just works. As a side note: yes, almost everything is still red in the MainActivity.
@galloperx If that <meta-data> tag is something added by Flutter then you should report it to the Flutter repo, flutter/flutter. It wasn't added by the IDE (unless I forgot something).

@stevemessick 
Yes, my Flutter App is working normally, only showing red in 'Flutter Project Window'
Thanks for the confirmation. I'm closing this because we've already published the work-around (open the Android module as a project in its own window) and don't have plans to address it further.
